    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "> Now that we have an object, it might be interesting to remove items as the first parameter in the next major and move it to the metadata object. Should we deprecate it now?\r\n\r\nI don't think that is needed. In most cases you want do do something like `items => items.map`, changing that to `({items}) => items.map` doesn't seem more friendly. Also I'm not sure how putting it in the second argument would help deprecation, as code would still need to change if we remove the first argument in a major",
